features: Hands-free one shoulder bakpack that can be worn as a crossbody or sling backpack for easy-access to everyday essentials like phones and wallets

body.description: Sling your gear on your back and get to work with the Mono Sling by Carhartt. Wear it on your back when you are on the go. And when you need access to the contents inside, just sling it around and grab what you need without ever taking it off. It's the perfect everyday crossbody pack to keep your essential gear close by, hands-free.The main compartment has ample space for books and folders- plus a padded tablet sleeve. The easy-access front pocket is perfect for small items and even includes a key fob. There's an additional hidden fleece-lined side pocket to store valuables like your sunglasses or cell phone. The adjustable padded mono shoulder strap has a side release buckle closure that makes throwing it on a cinch. Made with 600D polyester, this backpack is durable enough to toss in your truck and haul throughout the day. The Carhartt Rain Defender works to keep your gear dry in light rain. The water beads up and rolls right off. This casual crossbody measures 9 in W x 19 in H x 5 in L.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Lightweight Backpack for Developers on the Go
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased this lightweight backpack for my daily commute to work in the city, and I must say I'm impressed with it so far. The backpack is incredibly light, making it comfortable to carry around. The texture and quality of the material used are promising, and I believe it will hold up well over time.What had me keep the backpack is how it accommodates the new Apple silicone 14 Pro machines. My laptop fits snugly with some room to spare for a potential laptop sleeve or case. Along with the laptop, I can comfortably fit my keyboard, trackpad, and chargers without any issues. The sling type design suits my preference for a sleek and minimalist bag that doesn't compromise on functionality. (The brand patch is also easy to remove)However, while there are enough openings and pockets for most items, you may find it beneficial to invest in an additional organizer to keep your smaller accessories in order (not a requirement).Despite this minor drawback, I can recommend this backpack, especially for developers or anyone looking to travel light. Its compact size combined with the ability to carry essential devices makes it an excellent choice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: PROS:- The only side-open sling bag with tablet capacity I could find.- Fits all my daily needs, including an iPad Pro 11” (12” may or may not fit, it was tight with the Magic Keyboard on), chargers, multiple personal care items, phone, wallet, traveller’s journal, etc.- Everything fits flat and carries very comfortably.- Has a loop to secure any excess strap.- Really like the mesh zip section in the front pocket.NEUTRALS:- The material is a lot thinner than I was expecting from Carhartt. Not terrible since this helps lighten it, but I was expecting thicker.- It has a plastic buckle. Wasn’t expecting any different at this price point, but I prefer metal.- Collects dirt like crazy. I’m not new to black bags, and this one feels like a magnet for dirt prints. UPDATE: I was proved wrong. It will hold some contrasting dirt occasionally, but it stays clean for the most part. This is updated to a non-issue.- UPDATE: The hidden pocket will only hold keys OR a phone, probably an iPhone 14 Pro Max at most. Wider phones may run into issues fitting (such as the Duo).CONS:- It definitely runs small! I wear a men’s medium/women’s large and have a large bust - there’s only a few more inches of strap to expand it. I do tend to sit my packs lower, but even so I’m concerned about being able to wear it with any sort of heavy jacket.- The iPad/tablet pocket is pretty tight for an 11” iPad Pro, especially with a case. It can be awkward to maneuver in or out, especially with other items in the bag. (I’m not convinced this is entirely a con, because it seems inevitable to have the bag keep its size/shape, which I love). But you won’t be able to fit anything wider. UPDATE: I’ve taken to just leaving my iPad out of the slot if I have a lot of other items in the bag because it’s so awkward to get in. Hasn’t been a problem doing this though, other than general organization.INFO:- I couldn’t find ANY pictures of the interior pockets; I included some here. For those with vision impairment, the main pocket has a half-length padded tablet pocket on the back, and a half-length mesh on the front. The front pocket has a zippered mesh pocket across the length in the front and is otherwise open. There is also a ‘hidden’ fleece (?) lined side pocket for your wallet/phone/misc.CONCLUSION:- I love it. It’s going to be my daily for on-the-go and hoping it has good longevity. UPDATE: Still my everyday bag. I love this thing.
Nice bag. Not a big bag, but good for a lunch and iPad or chromebook.

Si bien Carhart se carecteriza por la notable calidad de sus productos y prendas en esta mochila en particular se nota una diferencia. la tela, como mencione, a diferencia de otras prendas es un poco delgada, sin embargo basta tocarla para saber que es un producto sumamente duradero, lo cierres son de una calidad increible, la resistencia al agua deja que desear, quiza es su punto mas debil. las costuras son solidads y reforzadas, el broche es bueno sin llegar a ser increible. los acabados internos son sumamente buenos y si meten algun articulo electronico no se rayara. tiene mas bolsas y compartimentos que no se muestran, asi como un gancho para las llaves, quiza otro punto debil es que si llevas alrrededor de 6 a 8 kilos se buelve un poco incomodo.en general es un 5 pero en especifico por dos o tres cuestiones que comente es un 4.5 pero aun asi, esta por ariba de muchos bolsos o mochilas.
La calidad es buena pero es de un material muy delgado
